, "updated_at": "2017-08-08T19:22:42Z", "closed_at": "2017-08-08T19:22:42Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/pulls/11622", "html_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/11622", "diff_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/11622.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/11622.patch"}, "body_html": "<p>NB: Changes the public API, albeit in a backwards-compatible way.</p>\n<p>Especially when copying variables between scopes it's handy to be able to grab sets of variables by scope. This allows the much more succinct:</p>\n<p><code>tf.trainable_variables(\"myscope\")</code></p>\n<p>which is equivalent to:</p>\n<p><code>tf.get_collection(tf.GraphKeys.TRAINABLE_VARIABLES, \"myscope\")</code></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Also fixup a minor unrelated documentation bug.</li>\n</ul>", "body_text": "NB: Changes the public API, albeit in a backwards-compatible way.\nEspecially when copying variables between scopes it's handy to be able to grab sets of variables by scope. This allows the much more succinct:\ntf.trainable_variables(\"myscope\")\nwhich is equivalent to:\ntf.get_collection(tf.GraphKeys.TRAINABLE_VARIABLES, \"myscope\")\n\nAlso fixup a minor unrelated documentation bug.", "body": "NB: Changes the public API, albeit in a backwards-compatible way.\r\n\r\nEspecially when copying variables between scopes it's handy to be able to grab sets of variables by scope. This allows the much more succinct:\r\n\r\n``tf.trainable_variables(\"myscope\")``\r\n\r\nwhich is equivalent to:\r\n\r\n``tf.get_collection(tf.GraphKeys.TRAINABLE_VARIABLES, \"myscope\")``\r\n\r\n- Also fixup a minor unrelated documentation bug."}